GRINNELL, IA. , Joseph
premier Wall, Parker Professor of History and Dean of
Grinnell College, is the author of a major new biography
of Andrew Carnegie published
today (Oct. 5) by Oxford Un—
identity Press.
A prespublication review of
the book in "Publishers’Weekly" acclaims it as "a maS*
terry study of the great empire-builder, and philanthropr
ist, and an increasing chronicle of the rise of Big music
news in the U.S.”
A product of 12 years of intensive research and writing,
the book is called by review
er Matthew robertson as
"without question one of the
absent works ofAmerican biographyﬂ‘
COMPLETE LIFE
The 1150*page volume is the
first modern and complete
life of the industrial giant to
appear in more man 40years.
It is the only work to make
use of the private correspondence of Carnegie and. his
wife, Louise, and of his early
business files and letter books
now in the possession of the
U.S. Steel Corporation and
never before accessible to
scholars.
