Debate Centers 0n Requirements
This summer a specialcommittee of 11 faculty and ad
ministrators studied several
plans for curriculum reform,
concentration on a11~college
requirements, with the intent
of representing specific
proposals for curriculum reform to the faculty this fall.
The study group was unable to
reach a consensus on a gen'
oral plan formal requirements,
but it did suggestseverai specsﬁc changes in the present
structure which were adopted
by the faculty to be effective
immediately.
The .committee grew from
the desire of faculty mem—
bars and students lastsemester to reevaluate the present
curriculum as it concerned
allrcollege requirements-and
