Group Stays Summer
With the early closing ofthis
college last May, a critical
view of the contemporaryedu»
national process was under
taken. One of the results of
this analysis was the forms
tion of the Grinnell Freedom
School this pastsummeri This
school was formed by a small
group of Students concerned
with the goals and the means
of the educational process.
According to one of the participants, the purpose of the
school was to study the concepts of radical politics, to
crystalize‘these concepts by
an investigation of materials
of interest to radicals, and
ultimately to develop the abiv
city to communicate these ideas to the populace at large.
Approximately fighters SIU’
cents participated on a full
time basis with a few faculty
members intermittently being
involved. The basic means of
achieving the specified goals
was through the formation of
a collective. With this struct
sure, the group was able to
place a special emphasis on
elimination the conditional
behavior installed into individuals by contemporary Ame
erican Society. Specifically,
the emphasis was placed on
the position of the woman in
today’s world, and her function in relation to the collect
time living situation. imperial
women's campus met to fur'
they the understandingof “women's generation” both in re
nation to collective living and
society in general.The experiences and results of the school are currently being published in a report which Shall
be distributed to college officials, students, and underground newspapers. Theaccomplishments of the group were
summer up as: an increase in
the knowledge of radical polar
trials, a better developed inn
tellectual concept of thesepolitics and the establishment of
a favorites living situation,
utilities the concepts which
had been studied.
